title: For Sale:  Compensators with Muzzle Couplings
postcontent:
I have a few pairs of what I call "high volume compensators" paired with muzzle couplings for specific Ruger models. The compensators are empty tubes that allow the gas to expand and cool, then to vent upwards through ports in the end of the tube. This reduces felt recoil and muzzle rise to keep you on target.  They are threaded 1/2x20.  There is a set screw on the rear bushing that lets you rotate the tube to position the vents upward.

The muzzle couplings allow you to use these threaded compensators without having threaded barrels.  The couplings fit over the end of the barrel with a slot for the front site.  Then, two split rings can be tightened up against the rear of the front site to lock the coupling in place and providing a 1/2x20 thread for accessories.
All parts are blued steel.  Ruger items shown in pictures are not included.  Couplings and compensators only.

I have three pairs I am willing to sell.  (1) A 5" compensator with a coupling for a MarkII with a std 4.5" bbl. (2) A 5" compensator for a MarkII with a 10" Bull Target bbl (round, slightly tapered, not flat). (3) A 6" compensator with a coupling for a 10/22 std bbl and a flash suppressor.

$100 each or $250 for all three pairs.

postcontent:
High Standard Flight King sold with Sears brand name in the 1960's. 28" plain modified choke barrel. This gun was not used on more than a couple dozen occassions over its nearly 50 year life. Not a spec of rust anywhere, bluing is nearly perfect. 

It's been kept oiled and sitting on a gunrack. This gun predates the Gun Control Act of 1968 and never had a serial number. I've never weighed this gun, but it is very light---feels like under six pounds. 20 gauge pump action shotgun. This is a one family gun since new---I used it a few times myself in the mid 1970's.
